content:
Enable users to select from multiple items by adding the Multi-select element to your OmniScript. Display options vertically, horizontally, or as an image.

Drag a Multi-select element from the Build panel onto the canvas.
In the Properties panel, give the element a name in the Name field and enter a label visible to the user.

(Optional) In Display Mode, select how to display the radio buttons:
- Horizontal: (Default) Display radio buttons next to each other.
- Vertical: Display radio buttons stacked.
- Image: Display each radio button as an image. Read-only Multi-Select element images render in grayscale.

If you select Image, configure Width, Height, and Image Count In Row.

In Option Source, select where the list of options come from:
- Manual: Manually enter value/label pairs.
- Custom: Enter the Apex class and method that returns the options.
- SObject: Retrieves the picklist values from the Salesforce object and field.
- Image: Manually enter value/label pairs and upload images to display.

For each option, click + Add New Option and enter Value and visible Label. Select an image or upload a new one. Check Use as Default to select the option by default.

If you select Custom or SObject as an Option Source, define the source of the controlling field and enter an Apex class.

(Optional) Configure Controlling Field Type to display options based on another value's selection.

For additional properties, see Common OmniScript Element Properties Definitions.
title: Configuring OmniScripts Multi-Select Element
